➕Types of Real Estate Investments & their benefits:

🏠Homeownership
Benefit: Many investors get their first real estate experience. They can develop a thorough understanding of the sector while beginning to accumulate money through equity.

🏡Residential Real Estate
Benefit: Passive income, which is normally obtained through monthly rental payments, is also available to you as the investor if you purchase income property through rentals.

🏙Commercial Real Estate
Benefit: Longer leases are quite advantageous for commercial real estate. Businesses that occupy a space often wish to remain there until they are established. Longer leases are more stable and reliable for the investor.

🏫Private Equity:
Benefit: Private equity or ownership has the benefit of flexibility. Private equity is not restricted to the same red tape that financial institutions are bound to in purchasing and selling real estate.

🏦Real Estate Investment Trusts:
Benefit: Investment in a REIT, you give a group of industry experts the authority to manage your funds among a variety of properties they hold, oversee, and eventually sell in order to boost your dividends and overall return.

🏭Industrial Real Estate:
Benefit: Investing in industrial real estate has the benefit of being in a high demand market. With many businesses focused on their online market place, shipping and manufacturing facilities are an absolute need.

🏪Retail Real Estate
Benefit: One major benefit of investing in retail real estate is that an investor can collect a percentage of the tenant’s monthly sales in addition to a rental fee.

🏘Mixed Use:
Benefit: Variety and diversity are two advantages of investing in mixed-use real estate. Because of its convenient location, mixed-use properties can scale up their rent. Additionally, with a mix of commercial and residential properties occupancy, the investor can benefit from a balanced real estate investment portfolio.
